   <abstract>Map from James Adair's History of the American Indians. It shows the location of various tribes across much of present-day eastern United States. Rivers, mountains, tribal towns, and forts are all denoted. One of the most important and detailed early maps of Native American tribes published.</abstract>
   <abstract>James Adair was an Irish trader who spent many years living with Southeastern tribes, primarily the Chickasaw. His book History of the American Indians, published in 1775, was one the most important 18th century works that examined Native Americans. Many of his ideas were subsequently discounted due to his argument that Native Americans were one of the lost tribes of Israel.</abstract>
